pageTitle: ‘Waddy Werewolf’ meeting packs local Ruritan Club | TheAndersonNews.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {26220=The Anderson News | circulation@theandersonnews.com | 502-839-6906 P.O. Box 410, 504 W. Broadway, Suite D, Lawrenceburg, KY 40342 Office Hours are 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Monday through Friday, 34357=Copyright © 2015, 20405=By Todd Martin The Sentinel-News WADDY – Residents seem convinced that the recent brutal maulings of several animals in southeast Shelby County were the blood-thirsty attacks of nothing more than a dog. Most of more than 100 residents and community who attended a meeting Monday night at the Waddy Ruritan Club, expressed certainty that a rogue dog, or dogs, is responsible for the mauled calves and goats, at least five of which have had to be euthanized, which were found between Nov. 30 and Dec. 6. And now there could be confirmation coming.}
